**Description 73: USA Estimated Real Rates (1970-1990)**
- **Blue line**: USA Avg Interest Rate Minus Headline Inflation
- **Red line**: USA Avg Interest Rate Minus GDP Deflator
- Both show sharp increases early 1980s, peaking ~8%
- Steady decline toward 1990s
- Dashed horizontal line marks long-term average of 2%

**Description 74: Unemployment and Equity Prices (1995-2010)**
- **Left graph** (Unemployment Rate): red line, 4% to 10%
- Three annotated periods: (1) decline 1995-2000, (2) rise 2000-2003, (3) decline until 2007, sharp increase to 10% by 2010
- Gray vertical line: "Short Rates Hit 0 percent"
- **Right graph** (Equity Prices Indexed, Jan 2000): S&P 500 (blue), MSCI ACWI (red), NASDAQ (green)
